   LITTON INDUSTRIES Inc. began an offering of $1 billion
face value of zero-coupon bonds, called liquid yield option
notes, due Sept. 26, 2010. The Beverly Hills, Calif., defense
and marine systems company will make the offering via Merrill
Lynch Capital Markets. The offering is expected to raise
about $258 million in net proceeds which the diversified
technology concern will use to pay debt. The bonds, which
have an annual yield to maturity of 6.75%, are convertible at
a rate of 3.063 shares of common stock per note, representing
an initial conversion price of $86.54.
